Merdeka Financial Services Group Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jun 26, 2017
May 25 17
Merdeka Financial Services Group Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jun 26, 2017, at 11:00 China Standard Time. Location: Jasmine Room, 3/F., Best Western Plus Hotel Hong Kong 308 Des Voeux Road Wes Hong Kong Hong Kong Agenda: To receive and adopt the audited consolidated financial statements of the company and the reports of the directors and auditors for the year ended 31 December 2016; to re-elect Mr. Au-yeung Sei Kwok as director of the Company; to re-elect Ms. Yeung Mo Sheung, Ann as director of the Company; to authorize the board of directors to fix directors' remuneration for the year ending 31 December 2017; to re-appoint Messrs. Elite Partners CPA Limited as auditors and authorise the board of directors to fix their remuneration; to grant a general mandate to the directors to allot, issue and deal with additional shares not exceeding 20% of the issued share capital of the Company; and to grant a general mandate to the directors to repurchase shares not exceeding 10% of the issued share capital of the Company.


Merdeka Financial Services Group Limited Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 8 17
Merdeka Financial Services Group Limited reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company has reported revenue was HKD 63,444,000 compared to HKD 48,912,000 for the same quarter ended March 31, 2016. The increased revenue was mainly contributed by trading business which increased approximately HKD 13.0 million to reach approximately HKD 48.6 million and financial services business which also increased approximately HKD 1.7 million to reach approximately HKD 14.7 million. Loss before tax was HKD 7,161,000 compared to HKD 9,703,000 for the same quarter ended March 31, 2016. Loss for the period was HKD 7,559,000 compared to HKD 9,758,000 for the same quarter ended March 31, 2016. Loss attributable to owners of the company was HKD 8,184,000 or 0.005 cents per basic and diluted share compared to HKD 9,532,000 or 0.007 cents per basic and diluted share for the same quarter ended March 31, 2016.


